    <note type="biography">
        <p>Dutch physician, anatomist, physiologist, and zoologist. Resident physician at the Buitengasthuis, Amsterdam, 1821. Professor of anatomy and physiology, University of Utrecht, 1827–62. Governor of the Utrechtsehe Dolhuis, 1827; inspector of lunatic asylums, 1842–62. Involved in reforms in the care of the mentally ill.</p></note>
